<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="SR0002" sponsor="Evan J. Vickers" designation="SR" otherSponsor="" otherHouse="House" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL1097" date="12/23/2025 11:12:217" printDate="12-23 11:51" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="srules"><info><nextbuid>3</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="01/01/1800"><seclist><sect action="A" src="rule" buid="1" uid="SR3-2-S402_1800010118000101" fromuid="SR3-2-S402_2024021420240501" sort="S03 02 04020018000101" mtype="section" effdate="01/01/1800">SR3-2-402</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="2" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="01/01/1800"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Senate Rules Resolution - Standing Committee Duties</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Evan J. Vickers</sponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><cn numlevel="1" lineno="4" slineno="0-4">Committee Note:<comrec voteid="38300" comcode="INTBUS" numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5"> The Business and Labor Interim Committee recommended this bill.<legvote numlevel="1" lineno="6" slineno="0-6">Legislative Vote:<yes>11 voting for</yes><no>0 voting against</no><abs>9 absent</abs></legvote></comrec></cn><gdhead lineno="7">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8">This rules resolution modifies the duties of a Senate standing committee.</gd><hphead lineno="9">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10">This resolution:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11" level="1">defines terms;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" level="1">when considering legislation that proposes to make an occupation a regulated occupation, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13"/>requires a Senate standing committee to determine whether the Office of Professional <ln numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14"/>Licensure Review conducted a sunrise review of the occupation; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15" level="1">makes technical and conforming changes.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="17">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="19">None</ocNone><ra numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20">Legislative Rules Affected:<raamd numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="SR3-2-402" src="rule" uid="SR3-2-S402_1800010118000101" buid="1" sort="S03 02 04020018000101" numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="0-22"><bold>SR3-2-402</bold>, </sn></raamd></ra></lt><enacthead lineno="23"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="0-24">Be it resolved by the Senate of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="SR3-2-402" type="amend" src="rule" uid="SR3-2-S402_1800010118000101" sort="S03 02 04020018000101" numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="SR3-2-402" numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="25">Section 1. <bold>SR3-2-402</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="26"><bold>SR3-2-402<parens/>. Standing committee consideration of legislation -- Regulated <ln numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-3"/>occupation -- Fiscal impact.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-3" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-5" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="17" groupid="16" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">As used in this rule:</amend><subsection ssid="1-4" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-6" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="20" groupid="18" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">"Office" means the Office of Professional Licensure Review created in Utah Code <ln numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-7"/>Title 13, Chapter 1b, Office of Professional Licensure Review.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-5" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="23" groupid="20" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">"Regulated occupation" means the same as that term is defined in Utah Code Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="13-1b-101"><ln numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-9"/>13-1b-101</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-8" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-10" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="32" groupid="26" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">When considering legislation that proposes to make an occupation a regulated <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-11"/>occupation, a standing committee shall determine whether the office conducted a sunrise <ln numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-12"/>review of the occupation in accordance with Utah Code Title 13, Chapter 1b, Part 3, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-13"/>Office Review and Reporting.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-2" dnum="_-o:3-i" numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-14" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both">(3)</amend></display>Except as provided in <xref depth="3" refnumber="SR3-2-401">SR3-2-401</xref>, a standing committee in one or both chambers <ln numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-15"/>shall <amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="37" groupid="30" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="both">review</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="36" groupid="29" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">consider</amend> legislation before the legislation is held in the opposite chamber <ln numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-16"/>because of the legislation's fiscal impact.</subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="2" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="false" numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="41">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="42"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both">This resolution takes effect upon a successful vote for final passage.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>12-23-25 11:51 AM</tm></rev></foot></leg>